#. <a class="nya" id="nya17"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.39"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "mn7:17.1"
msgid ""
"So ‘atthi idaṃ, atthi hīnaṃ, atthi paṇītaṃ, atthi imassa saññāgatassa uttari "
"nissaraṇan’ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""

#. <a class="nya" id="nya18"></a>
msgctxt "mn7:18.1"
msgid ""
"Tassa evaṃ jānato evaṃ passato kāmāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati, bhavāsavāpi "
"cittaṃ vimuccati, avijjāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn7:18.2"
msgid "Vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn7:18.3"
msgid ""
"‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti "
"pajānāti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn7:18.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn7:18.5"
msgid "‘bhikkhu sināto antarena sinānenā’”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya19"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "mn7:19.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena sundarikabhāradvājo brāhmaṇo bhagavato avidūre "
"nisinno hoti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn7:19.2"
msgid "Atha kho sundarikabhāradvājo brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn7:19.3"
msgid "“gacchati pana bhavaṃ gotamo bāhukaṃ nadiṃ sināyitun”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn7:19.4"
msgid "“Kiṃ, brāhmaṇa, bāhukāya nadiyā?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn7:19.5"
msgid "Kiṃ bāhukā nadī karissatī”ti?"
msgstr ""

# BB has “liberation”, obviously following PTS in reading “mokkhasammata”. This reading is supported by MA 93, which has 度相. (The other Chinese parallel at T 51 doesn’t have a close parallel with this phrase.) However the comm evidently reads lokkha: Tattha lokkhasammatāti lūkhabhāvasammatā, lūkhabhāvanti cokkhabhāvaṃ, visuddhibhāvaṃ detīti evaṃ sammatāti vuttaṃ hoti. The problem is that lokkha gives the exact opposite sense: rough or dirty. Nor does there appear to be any supporting sense in Sanskrit. The PTS dict suggests reading cokkha=clean here: https://suttacentral.net/define/cokkha, and I think this is the best reading. Liberation doesn’t fit the imagery of the text. Nor, so far as I know, was it generally held among the brahmins that liberation came from bathing alone. On the contrary, it is precisely those brahmins who developed the notion of liberation who insisted on the inner understanding. I suspect the Chinese translation, therefore, is a normalization, as is the reading mokkha in the Pali.
#. VAR: Lokkhasammatā → lokhyasammatā (bj) | lokasammatā (s1-3) | mokkhasammatā (pts1)
msgctxt "mn7:19.6"
msgid ""
"“Lokkhasammatā hi, bho gotama, bāhukā nadī bahujanassa, puññasammatā hi, bho "
"gotama, bāhukā nadī bahujanassa, bāhukāya pana nadiyā bahujano pāpakammaṃ "
"kataṃ pavāhetī”ti."
msgstr ""

#. <a class="nya" id="nya20"></a>
msgctxt "mn7:20.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā sundarikabhāradvājaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ gāthāhi ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "mn7:20.2"
msgid "“Bāhukaṃ adhikakkañca,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
#. VAR: sundarikaṃ mapi → sundarikāmapi (bj, s1-3, pts1) | sundarikaṃ mahiṃ (itipi)
msgctxt "mn7:20.3"
msgid "gayaṃ sundarikaṃ mapi;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn7:20.4"
msgid "Sarassatiṃ payāgañca,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn7:20.5"
msgid "atho bāhumatiṃ nadiṃ;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
#. VAR: pakkhando → pakkhanno (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "mn7:20.6"
msgid "Niccampi bālo pakkhando,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn7:20.7"
msgid "kaṇhakammo na sujjhati."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "mn7:20.8"
msgid "Kiṃ sundarikā karissati,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
#. VAR: payāgā → payāgo (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "mn7:20.9"
msgid "Kiṃ payāgā kiṃ bāhukā nadī;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn7:20.10"
msgid "Veriṃ katakibbisaṃ naraṃ,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn7:20.11"
msgid "Na hi naṃ sodhaye pāpakamminaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "mn7:20.12"
msgid "Suddhassa ve sadā phaggu,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn7:20.13"
msgid "Suddhassuposatho sadā;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn7:20.14"
msgid "Suddhassa sucikammassa,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn7:20.15"
msgid "Sadā sampajjate vataṃ;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn7:20.16"
msgid "Idheva sināhi brāhmaṇa,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn7:20.17"
msgid "Sabbabhūtesu karohi khemataṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "mn7:20.18"
msgid "Sace musā na bhaṇasi,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn7:20.19"
msgid "sace pāṇaṃ na hiṃsasi;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn7:20.20"
msgid "Sace adinnaṃ nādiyasi,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn7:20.21"
msgid "saddahāno amaccharī;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn7:20.22"
msgid "Kiṃ kāhasi gayaṃ gantvā,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn7:20.23"
msgid "udapānopi te gayā”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya21"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.40"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "mn7:21.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, sundarikabhāradvājo brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn7:21.2"
msgid "“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn7:21.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bho gotama, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā "
"vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya—"
"cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantīti; evamevaṃ bhotā gotamena anekapariyāyena "
"dhammo pakāsito."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn7:21.4"
msgid "Esāhaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn7:21.5"
msgid ""
"Labheyyāhaṃ bhoto gotamassa santike pabbajjaṃ, labheyyaṃ upasampadan”ti."
msgstr ""

#. <a class="nya" id="nya22"></a>
msgctxt "mn7:22.1"
msgid ""
"Alattha kho sundarikabhāradvājo brāhmaṇo bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ, "
"alattha upasampadaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn7:22.2"
msgid ""
"Acirūpasampanno kho panāyasmā bhāradvājo eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī "
"pahitatto viharanto nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā "
"anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme "
"sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn7:22.3"
msgid ""
"“Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā”ti "
"abbhaññāsi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn7:22.4"
msgid "Aññataro kho panāyasmā bhāradvājo arahataṃ ahosīti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn7:22.5"
msgid "Vatthasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
